Happy Valentine’s Day @terryltam 😏😈

I am proud of me.

It’s hard sometimes to fight for the awareness of mental illnesses most people don’t care about and don’t take seriously. 

I took on a battle that is not easy, that contradicts ideologies that were created hundreds of years ago, that contradicts our beliefs regarding beauty standards and body image. 

I get criticised for it, I get judged, I receive insults and mockeries everyday for the fight I decided to take on. 

But you know what ? I don’t care.
I know who I am.

I am someone who went through one of the hardest battles there exists in the world of illnesses and decided to help others recover when I came out of it.

So no, I’m not going to stop talking about fatphobia.
No, I’m not going to stop talking about eating disorders.
No, I’m not going to stop showing my body, my cellulite, my stretch marks and my flab. 
No, I’m not going to stop celebrating my sexuality.

The work I do is hard as hell but most importantly, it is absolutely ESSENTIAL.

I write my own story. 
That’s it. 

❤️

#mentalhealth #selflove #bodyimage #bodyacceptance #mentalhealthawareness
Self Love is your Power ❤️

✨ You have to be comfortable with being uncomfortable ✨

This is the first rule to learn how to love ourselves. 

We are conditioned to be so many things that are influenced by society, so much so that we forget we can be our own whole person. 

These pictures are not “socially acceptable”. They are not “ socially flattering”. They are not what society qualifies as beauty standards.

❤️ But you are more than what society tells you you should be. ❤️

This is my body, good angle, bad angle, I don’t care. 
It’s my home. 
It’s my cocoon. 
It’s the vessel that allows me to live and breathe.

So who cares if it doesn’t look like beauty standards or beauty ideals ? 
Not me !

I am comfortable with being uncomfortable because I am learning so much about what my body can be and do for me. 

You can be so much more than what society has been telling you that women should be. So, so much more. 

Self love begins with being uncomfortable. 
So take the picture. 
Wear the lingerie. 
Wear the bikini. 
Allow your body to just be ❤️

You are and have so much to offer ✨

10 years ago, I wanted to get liposuction on my hips and stomach, I was restricting severely to stay thin, I would go to the gym for hours after eating a pizza.

It seemed impossible to recover from my ED. It seemed impossible for me to love my body as it is.

When I realised I couldn’t live like this anymore because being thin wasn’t actually making me happier, I knew I had to heal from my past trauma and allow myself to let love in. 

I had to learn that I am allowed to love myself and that I am allowed to feel beautiful in my own skin. 

You are allowed to love your body even if it doesn’t look like beauty standards. You are allowed you are allowed you are allowed. 

❤️

Be curious, ask questions, try to help them see that they need healing.
And if they don’t want to change, then you can leave ❤️

My whole life I’ve given my loyalty and my love to people who took advantage of it. To people who stayed when I was at my best and left when I was at my worst. 

I want to be surrounded with people who love as hard as I do. I want to be surrounded with people who see my worth even on bad days, even when I’m sick, even when I’m depressed. No matter how long it takes for me to get better. Because I would do that for them. 

I don’t think I will ever be able to give my love to people like I have before. An unconditional, caring, deep love.

I’ve heard the saying « not everybody has the same heart as you » 

And I know that now.

I deserve a partner who doesn’t leave me because my health issues are taking too long to get better, or because my depression gets too intense, or because I’m not always 100%, or because I’m not working as hard as I should be when life throws unusual circumstances at me.

Because I know my worth, I know that when I love someone, I give them all my love, through ups, downs, sickness, through mental health issues, money, no money, happiness, sadness, failure. 

Love isn’t a performance. Love isn’t based on your performance. 

I love unconditionally because if I let you into my life in the first place, I already know your worth, no matter what life throws at you.

And I deserve people who do that for me. 
I will never settle again for people who can’t. 

Thank you Universe, for not letting anything or anyone make me doubt my own worth and how valuable I am. 

Don’t you let anyone take your shine away from you. Don’t you let anyone convince you that you’re weak, stupid, unworthy, or unlovable.

No one can diminish you but yourself.

❤️

I am my biggest inspiration and I want YOU to be YOUR biggest inspiration ❤️

Every time I fall down, I remember every time that I have pulled myself back up. Every time I’m scared, I remember every time I have moved through fear. ☀️

I wouldn’t want to be anyone else than me, and I so want you to feel the same way about yourself 💕

Pay attention to what make your soul shine and do more of it ✨Pay attention to the people who want to see you shine 🌻 Pay attention to what makes your heart and your body happy 🌈

You have to work on your relationship with yourself to be invincible. It’s hard work, but it is so worth it.

Shine, shine, shine my darlings ❤️

I was taught my whole life to hate my love handles, directly or indirectly through friends, the media, tv shows, advertisements. 

I was waiting to turn 18 to get liposuction, and today at 31 years old, I am so grateful that I never altered my body. 

The parts of me that I used to be so ashamed of and angry at are parts of my body that I cherish and love so much today. Because it makes me who I am. 

The beauty of human beings is that we are all so different, that’s what makes the world interesting and rich, it’s how different we all are, in body shape, colour, culture, food. This world is so rich.

And I think it’s such a shame to convince women that they should look a certain way to be considered beautiful. That’s not reality. It’s a social construct that we don’t have to listen to and obey.

Look at the parts of yourself that you don’t like and ask yourself, really think about why you don’t like them. Is it innate, or was it influenced by society ? Think about the ways society and the media condition us to hate parts of our body and go against that.

You should be so proud to be and to look different from other people. 
It’s what makes you YOU!

Be proud of you ❤️
